00:06:09.360 --> 00:06:14.750
I think, has merit and still
resonates with the idea

00:06:14.750 --> 00:06:19.390
that the world is alive,
it's pulsing, it's speaking

00:06:19.390 --> 00:06:24.380
to us all the time if we
know how to listen to it.

00:06:25.480 --> 00:06:31.390
And there are actually
hints about that idea,

00:06:31.390 --> 00:06:33.910
the world speaking
to us from the past.

00:06:33.910 --> 00:06:41.890
So, for example, in Imperial
Japan, the emperor dressed

00:06:41.890 --> 00:06:51.270
in full regalia with his entire
court would go out to Kyoto

00:06:51.270 --> 00:06:56.170
to Arashiyama which is a
sacred place near Kyoto

00:06:56.170 --> 00:07:01.370
and they would go for
one purpose, to listen.

00:07:01.370 --> 00:07:04.760
And what where they
listening for?

00:07:04.760 --> 00:07:08.440
Well, here's a clue, there's
a poem written in honor

00:07:08.440 --> 00:07:14.980
of what they were tuning into,
"If a jewel of dew could sing,

00:07:14.980 --> 00:07:17.910
it would tinkle with such
a voice" anybody want

00:07:17.910 --> 00:07:21.160
to guess what that might be?

00:07:23.510 --> 00:07:29.700
[ Cricket Sounds ]

00:07:29.700 --> 00:07:31.000
It's a cricket.

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:40.770
Whose emotions homoeogryllus
japonica, the bell cricket

00:07:40.770 --> 00:07:48.090
and the members of court

00:07:48.090 --> 00:07:50.840
of the emperor's court
would collect them

00:07:50.840 --> 00:07:52.970
and they'd take them
back and they would judge

00:07:52.970 --> 00:07:55.770
which one was the best singer
and even today, until today

00:07:55.770 --> 00:07:58.190
and in this time, in Japan
the collection and the keeping

00:07:58.190 --> 00:08:04.130
of crickets as pets is still
very much a tradition in Japan

00:08:04.130 --> 00:08:06.670
with keeping little cricket
cages and they release them

00:08:06.670 --> 00:08:10.620
around this time of year.

00:08:10.620 --> 00:08:15.150
But the idea as I was preparing
this talk and thinking about it

00:08:15.150 --> 00:08:18.990
and reminding myself about
that sound and that practice

00:08:18.990 --> 00:08:22.790
that was, in fact, one of the
Pulse of the Planet programs

00:08:22.790 --> 00:08:27.510
